Music affects people in various ways, including influencing mood, memory, and emotions. It can boost mood, reduce anxiety and depression, and enhance memory and task endurance. Music also affects neurotransmitters like dopamine and serotonin, which play a role in mood regulation. Additionally, music can increase blood flow to brain regions that control emotions and has been shown to have effects on cardiovascular function and athletic performance. However, it can also have harmful effects, such as inducing rumination.